## Local-only commit contract

- Use the repository's commit convention and targeted staging.
- Leave a clean worktree with at least one local commit.
- Never push or create a PR. The wrapper will run fresh local Claude and Codex
  reviews, integrate a fresh base, validate, push, and create the PR.
- Never bypass hooks with `--no-verify`.

## Security and privacy

- Never put PHI, PII, credentials, authorization headers, customer identifiers,
  internal hostnames, or user data in logs, issue comments, commits, or PR text.
- Do not copy issue bodies or reviewer output into publication metadata.
